javadoc:
Manages property values of type int, String, Object, and
 "void"  for a page of possible addresses. Void serves as a marker 
 for whether an address has a property. The derived class for each type holds
 the actual value of the property, and overrides the
 appropriate add() and get() methods.

methods.name: <init>
methods.comment: Constructor

params.name: pageSize
params.comment: max number of properties on this page

methods.name: getNext
methods.comment:
Returns the next offset after the given offset that has a property
   value.

methods.name: addKey
methods.comment:
Adds the key to the keySet. If all values are set,
 use FullBitSet.

params.name: key
params.comment: The key to be added to the set.

methods.name: getPrevious
methods.comment:
Return the previous offset (before offset) that has a
 property.

methods.javadoc: Return the first offset that has a property.
methods.name: getFirst
methods.comment: Return the first offset that has a property.

methods.javadoc: Return the last offset that has a property.
methods.name: getLast
methods.comment: Return the last offset that has a property.

methods.javadoc:
Return whether this page has any offset with
 a property.
methods.name: isEmpty
methods.comment:
Return whether this page has any offset with
 a property.

methods.javadoc:
Return whether the given offset has a property.
@param offset offset into the page
methods.name: hasProperty
methods.comment: Return whether the given offset has a property.

methods.name: getSaveableObject
methods.comment: Get the object property at the given offset.

methods.name: addSaveableObject
methods.comment: Add the object property at the given offset.

methods.name: getObject
methods.comment: Get the object property at the given offset.

methods.name: addObject
methods.comment: Add the object property at the given offset.

methods.name: getString
methods.comment: Get the String property at the given offset.

methods.name: addString
methods.comment: Add the String property at the given offset.

methods.name: getInt
methods.comment: Get the int property at the given offset.

methods.name: addInt
methods.comment: Add the int property at the given offset.

methods.name: getLong
methods.comment: Get the long property at the given offset.

methods.name: addLong
methods.comment: Add the long property at the given offset.

methods.name: getShort
methods.comment: Get the short property at the given offset.

methods.name: addShort
methods.comment: Add the short property at the given offset.

methods.name: getByte
methods.comment: Get the long property at the given offset.

methods.name: addByte
methods.comment: Add the byte property at the given offset.

methods.name: add
methods.comment: Mark the given offset as having a property.

methods.name: addRange
methods.comment: Mark the given offset ranges as having a property.

methods.javadoc: Get the number of properties on this page.
methods.name: getSize
methods.comment: Get the number of properties on this page.

methods.name: remove
methods.comment: Remove the property at the given offset.

return.comment:
true if the property was removed; return false
 if there was not a property at offset
